[{"client_msg_id":"6de9b234-3c3f-40a6-bc98-fb48f3d45f15","type":"message","text":"Hi, I am trying to create a new column in my data frame. The source column is a `Date` and the target column should be a `string` with the year and the month. I have the following code\n```transform(cxvolume, :CREATED_ON =&gt; (a -&gt; Dates.format(a, \"mm yyyy\")) =&gt; :CREATED_ON_MONTH_YEAR)```\nbut i have this error message\n```MethodError: no method matching format(::SentinelArrays.ChainedVector{Dates.Date,Array{Dates.Date,1}}, ::String)```\nAny idea why?","user":"U01EZ6VN118","ts":"1616612004.222100","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"U01EZ6VN118","ts":"1616612042.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"al5","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Hi, I am trying to create a new column in my data frame. The source column is a "},{"type":"text","text":"Date","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and the target column should be a "},{"type":"text","text":"string","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" with the year and the month. I have the following code\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"transform(cxvolume, :CREATED_ON => (a -> Dates.format(a, \"mm yyyy\")) => :CREATED_ON_MONTH_YEAR)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"but i have this error message\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"MethodError: no method matching format(::SentinelArrays.ChainedVector{Dates.Date,Array{Dates.Date,1}}, ::String)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Any idea why?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616612004.222100","reply_count":6,"reply_users_count":4,"latest_reply":"1616620581.224200","reply_users":["U67SCG4HG","U680THK2S","U01EZ6VN118","UBF9YRB6H"],"is_locked":false,"subscribed":false},{"client_msg_id":"fd35edd9-d9b9-4d9e-a37b-5193e4f48cd6","type":"message","text":"I believe `a` that is passed is the whole column, so you need to broadcast the call to `format`. Try\n```transform(cxvolume, :CREATED_ON =&gt; (a -&gt; Dates.format.(a, \"mm yyyy\")) =&gt; :CREATED_ON_MONTH_YEAR)```\nmaybe?","user":"U67SCG4HG","ts":"1616612220.222500","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"bqs","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I believe "},{"type":"text","text":"a","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" that is passed is the whole column, so you need to broadcast the call to "},{"type":"text","text":"format","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Try\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"transform(cxvolume, :CREATED_ON => (a -> Dates.format.(a, \"mm yyyy\")) => :CREATED_ON_MONTH_YEAR)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"maybe?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616612004.222100","parent_user_id":"U01EZ6VN118","reactions":[{"name":"point_up","users":["U681ELA87"],"count":1},{"name":"slightly_smiling_face","users":["U01EZ6VN118"],"count":1}]},{"client_msg_id":"5187fc2f-bc1d-40f7-b9b1-4b18206f9586","type":"message","text":"(note the `.` in the call to `format`)","user":"U67SCG4HG","ts":"1616612231.222700","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"U67SCG4HG","ts":"1616612249.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"5aJ","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(note the "},{"type":"text","text":".","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" in the call to "},{"type":"text","text":"format","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616612004.222100","parent_user_id":"U01EZ6VN118"},{"client_msg_id":"3af7151e-84b6-41d6-8a06-fc25f8de32ea","type":"message","text":"Alternatively, you can wrap the `(a -&gt; ...)` in `ByRow`","user":"U680THK2S","ts":"1616612342.223100","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"5wu","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can wrap the "},{"type":"text","text":"(a -> ...)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"text","text":"ByRow","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616612004.222100","parent_user_id":"U01EZ6VN118","reactions":[{"name":"heavy_check_mark","users":["UBF9YRB6H","U01EZ6VN118"],"count":2}]},{"client_msg_id":"8aa5212e-7c10-4087-be8e-f31e564cb2d8","type":"message","text":"But either of those should work the same","user":"U680THK2S","ts":"1616612355.223300","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Pny","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"But either of those should work the same"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616612004.222100","parent_user_id":"U01EZ6VN118"},{"client_msg_id":"b46af40b-9218-43ae-bb0d-54ec2fac7b41","type":"message","text":"Thanks to both of you! More generally, every function that is used in a `transform` should either expect a column be broadcasted when expecting a single value -- is that right?","user":"U01EZ6VN118","ts":"1616618182.223700","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"wxY","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Thanks to both of you! More generally, every function that is used in a "},{"type":"text","text":"transform","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" should either expect a column be broadcasted when expecting a single value -- is that right?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616612004.222100","parent_user_id":"U01EZ6VN118"},{"client_msg_id":"37ad7589-ecae-4825-8207-24ba88c739f9","type":"message","text":"All functions should be written expecting vectors. If you have a function that is written to accept scalars, wrap in `ByRow`.","user":"UBF9YRB6H","ts":"1616620581.224200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Wm40","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"All functions should be written expecting vectors. If you have a function that is written to accept scalars, wrap in "},{"type":"text","text":"ByRow","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616612004.222100","parent_user_id":"U01EZ6VN118","reactions":[{"name":"thumbsup_all","users":["U01EZ6VN118"],"count":1}]}]